___________________________skia___________________________

--------------------------hints--------------------------

You can get ninja from 'github.com/ninja-build/ninja/releases'.
Do not use 'sudo apt-get install ninja', it is not the ninja you need.

Before running [2] make sure to install git.
For Ubuntu: sudo apt-get install git

Older versions of g++ may fail while compiling ([5] and [7]).
For Ubuntu 16.04:
|sudo add-apt-repository -y ppa:jonathonf/gcc
|sudo apt-get update
|sudo apt-get install g++-7
|[5] and [7] will use /usr/bin/g++ by default,
|you can for ex. replace /usr/bin/g++ with a link to /usr/bin/g++-7

In [5] and [7] replace '2' with number of threads you want to use,
note that linking can use lots of memory,
you can use all your threads for compiling (up until [~3000/x]),
then Ctrl+C to interrupt, and start again with low thread count.

-------------------------commands-------------------------
[0] tar xf skia.tar.xz
[1] cd skia
[2] python tools/git-sync-deps
[3] tools/install_dependencies.sh

### Only if you need debug build of enve
# [4] bin/gn gen out/Debug --args='extra_cflags=["-Wno-error"]'
# [5] ninja -C out/Debug -j 2
###

[6] bin/gn gen out/Release --args='is_official_build=true is_debug=false extra_cflags=["-Wno-error"]'
[7] ninja -C out/Release -j 2